tural Research -- t10. The Hyper-Local Development of Translanguaging Pedagogies -- t11. Collaborative and Participatory Research for Plurilingual Language Learning -- t12. Translanguaging as Practice and as Outcome: Bridging across Educational Milieus through a Collaborative Service-Learning Project -- tAfterword : Starting from the Other End -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book examines translanguaging as a resource which can disrupt the privileging of particular voices, and a social practice which enables collaboration within and across groups of people. Addressing the themes of collaboration and transformation, the chapters critically examine how people work together to catalyse change in diverse global contexts, experiences and traditions. The authors suggest an epistemological and methodological turn to the study of translanguaging, which is particularly reflected in the collaborative, arts-based and action research/activist approaches followed in the chapters. The book will be of particular interest to scholars using ethnographic, critical and collaborative action and activist research approaches to the study of multilingualism in educational and creative arts contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aTranslanguaging (Linguistics). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aQualitative research methods in multilingualism and education.  acodeswitching.  acollaboration.  acreative arts.  aeducation.  alinguistic diversity.  alinguistic ethnography.  amigration studies.  amultilingualism in creative arts contexts.  amultilingualism in educational contexts.  amultilingualism.  asociolinguistics.  atransformation.  atranslanguaging.1 aAden, Joëlle, econtributor.4ctb